    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## How to use（In this section, show an example to submit a short video (less than 3 minutes) for editing via API）\n1.  Obtain Your API Key, and repalce VIZARDAI_API_KEY of headers of node 'video editing create workflow' and ' vizard video editing query workflow'.\n2. Submit a Video for Editing ( https://docs.vizard.ai/docs/submit-a-short-video-for-editing ).\n3. Retrieve Your Clips（ https://docs.vizard.ai/docs/retrieve-video-clips ）.\n4. Check clip status by polling, or configure a webhook URL in workspace before submitting a video.\n##\n\nWhen you send a short video to Vizard for editing, there are 3 core settings you need in your API request.\n1. Tell Vizard You Want “Editing,” Not “Clipping”: \"getClips\": 0\n2. Tell Vizard Where Your Video Lives:\nvideoUrl + videoType\nWhen using a direct video file (videoType = 1) and Include the file extension: \"ext\": \"mp4\"( Supported extensions: mp4, 3gp, avi, mov )\n3. Tell Vizard What Language Is Spoken in the Video:\"lang\": \"auto\"( Most of the time, automatic detection is the easiest choice )\nsupport_language_list: https://vizard.readme.io/docs/supported-languages#/\n\n\n",
        "height": 352,
        "width": 1248
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
